FBIS4-32947 "drlat105_a_94018" FBIS-LAT-94-105 Daily Report 27 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Fuel Unloading Pipeline System Under Construction Fuel Unloading Pipeline System Under Construction FL2805111594 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 27 May 94 FL2805111594 Havana Radio Reloj Network Spanish BFN [Text] Experts from different organizations are at the Moa port, in Holguin Province, to construct a pipeline system for unloading and storing fuel to reduce transport costs and to benefit the Cuban nickel industry. This fuel pipeline will be approximately one km in length. It will be built on Moa Bay and will include the coupling of tubes up to 24 inches in diameter and secured in a field away from the docks. This system will facilitate the unloading of fuel from tankers of up to 75,000 tons in capacity which [words indistinct] the suppliers of fuel given the little depth of the old [word indistinct]. This complex work will allow the annual consumption of 300,000 tons of national crude oil by two of the three nickel plants and a cobalt plant which are operating in the northeastern part of Holguin.
